My model of investment banks is that they are socialist collectives run for=
 the benefit of their employees, but I confess that that is an outdated mod=
el. Once upon a time it was more or less literally true =E2=80=94=C2=A0the =
big investment banks were once private partnerships =E2=80=94=C2=A0and even=
 as public companies investment banks have sometimes had a tendency to run =
themselves for the enrichment of their employees rather than of shareholder=
s.=C2=A0But the industry is not what it used to be, banks care more about t=
heir shareholders now, and these days some of the big investment banks seem=
 positively skeptical of socialism.
For instance,=C2=A0the Financial Times reports:

Wall Street banks have warned that their next wave of hiring in France may =
be stunted without restrictions on dismissal costs for highly paid traders,=
 a flagship measure that has been left out of a reform package intended to =
bolster Paris as a financial centre. =E2=80=A6
Redundancy payouts to traders earning more than =E2=82=AC1mn a year in Pari=
s can end up being more than five times that of London, although there is l=
ess of a difference between France and the rest of Europe. =E2=80=A6
The idea under review would be to put more specific limits on payouts to tr=
aders so they don=E2=80=99t exceed a threshold of about half a million euro=
s. =E2=80=A6
Alexandre Holroyd, a lawmaker who is leading the reform package, said Franc=
e=E2=80=99s labour rules were meant to be protective, but had never been de=
signed to overcompensate traders.
=E2=80=9CA trading floor is somewhere where there is a lot of volatility an=
d variations in headcount,=E2=80=9D Holroyd said. =E2=80=9CIt=E2=80=99s the=
 flipside of being paid sums of money that are completely disproportionate =
to more than 99 per cent of people.=E2=80=9D

If you hire a trader and pay her more than a million euros a year, and she =
doesn=E2=80=99t work out, you=E2=80=99d like to be able to get rid of her w=
ithout paying her millions more. On the other hand, if you=C2=A0are=C2=A0a =
trader getting paid more than a million euros a year, and your bank decides=
 to get rid of you,=C2=A0you=E2=80=99d like to get paid millions more, no? =
Seems nicer.
Also there are risk-management considerations; Byrne Hobart notes:
High legally-mandated payouts for firing amount to a put option on their co=
mpensation. If they get a free put option, their incentive is to take more =
risk. Part of what banks are worried about is what it costs to fire an unde=
rperforming trader, but another thing it's prudent for them to worry about =
is how much it pays for a trader to underperform.
This is true as a matter of options math, but I wonder how true it is socio=
logically. Are French traders notably riskier than British or American ones=
? (There are tantalizing examples.) There is some baseline level of risk th=
at you have to take as a trader to=C2=A0avoid=C2=A0getting fired, and perha=
ps if getting fired is cushy enough your reaction will be laziness rather t=
han risk-taking.
Elsewhere, here is a claim that =E2=80=9Cthe hedge fund industry=E2=80=99s =
biggest stars are looking beyond money when they plot their career moves, a=
ccording to IDW Group founder and Chief Executive Officer Ilana Weinstein=
=E2=80=9D:

After a year or two of guaranteed compensation in a new role, =E2=80=9Cyou=
=E2=80=99re out and you=E2=80=99re on your own, so to speak, and you need t=
o put up the goods,=E2=80=9D Weinstein said Friday in a Bloomberg Televisio=
n interview. =E2=80=9CThe question becomes: Are you really set up for succe=
ss, how do you develop, and what are the resources the firm has to get you =
there?=E2=80=9D =E2=80=A6
=E2=80=9C=E2=80=98Will I be better by virtue of making this move, developme=
ntally =E2=80=94 will I be the best version of myself?=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D sh=
e said. =E2=80=9CThe second question is, =E2=80=98Is there more opportunity=
 at this place that I=E2=80=99m going to, relative to where I=E2=80=99m at?=
=E2=80=99=E2=80=9D

I feel like I=E2=80=99d probably be a better version with myself with=C2=A0=
more money.

