<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">A pretty standard story in crypto is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Crypto in general, and Crypto Project=
 X in particular, are=C2=A0<em>building something.=C2=A0</em>Each crypto pr=
oject is working to achieve some vision of=C2=A0the future of finance or co=
mmunications or media or wireless networking or whatever, and crypto collec=
tively =E2=80=94=C2=A0the aggregate of those projects =E2=80=94=C2=A0is mov=
ing toward some loosely shared vision of a future of decentralized ownershi=
p, censorship resistance, etc.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">By =
buying tokens of Crypto Project X, you are betting on the success of whatev=
er they are building: If the thing succeeds, the tokens will be worth more =
than you paid for them.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">
<em>Probably=C2=A0</em>the people building Crypto Project X are=C2=A0<em>se=
lling=C2=A0</em>its tokens to raise money to build the thing, or doing some=
thing that rhymes with that.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-5=
" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-=
width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !import=
ant; background-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[5]</span>
</a>
</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is not the only story in crypto; there is=
 another common story that <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.c=
om/click/34967840.259352/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydG=
ljbGVzLzIwMjQtMDMtMTgvc2xvcmctaXMtc29ycnktaGUtYnVybnQtc2xlcmY_Y21waWQ9QkJEM=
DQwODI0X01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXIm=
dXRtX3Rlcm09MjQwNDA4JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a2=
3cBa4178f57" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blan=
k" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom=
-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; back=
ground-color: #ccc;">goes like</a> =E2=80=9Csomeone created some tokens as =
a joke and now they are worth billions of dollars.=E2=80=9D But the one I l=
aid out above is important. For one thing, it describes a lot of big crypto=
 projects. Also, though, it would be hard to=C2=A0<em>care=C2=A0</em>about =
crypto if it=C2=A0<em>wasn=E2=80=99t </em>trying to build something. =E2=80=
=9CDogecoin is a joke and if you buy it it might go up=E2=80=9D is, I think=
, a very interesting fact about modern finance, but you=E2=80=99d feel sill=
y devoting your life to it.=C2=A0<em><a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomberg=
business.com/click/34967840.259352/aHR0cHM6Ly9yZWFkd3JpdGVvd24uY29tLw/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cB7627a25d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Read Write Own: Building the Next Era=
 of the Internet</a>=C2=A0</em>is the name of venture capitalist Chris Dixo=
n=E2=80=99s book about crypto, and if you are a venture capitalist =E2=80=
=9Cthe next era of the internet=E2=80=9D is a better thing to back than =E2=
=80=9Ca joke about a dog.=E2=80=9D</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The problem with this story, though, is that C=
rypto Project X=E2=80=99s tokens sure sound like they are <em>securities=C2=
=A0</em>under US law. A <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/=
click/34967840.259352/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljb=
GVzLzIwMjMtMDctMTQvcmlwcGxlLWlzLWEtc2VjdXJpdHktYW5kLWl0LWlzbi10P2NtcGlkPUJC=
RDA0MDgyNF9NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGV=
yJnV0bV90ZXJtPTI0MDQwOCZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a31=
9a23cB0171f8e2" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_b=
lank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bot=
tom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; b=
ackground-color: #ccc;">security is</a> =E2=80=9Can investment of money in =
a common enterprise with profits to come solely from the efforts of others,=
=E2=80=9D and what I laid out above =E2=80=94=C2=A0Crypto Project X is a gr=
oup of people building a thing, they raise money by selling tokens, and you=
 buy tokens hoping to make money if their thing succeeds =E2=80=94=C2=A0is =
that.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">US securities law exists mostly to prevent swi=
ndling in the sale of securities. This=C2=A0creates several problems for cr=
ypto:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Some crypto projects are in fact swin=
dles, and securities law is bad for them.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom=
: 5px;">The main way that the law prevents swindles is by requiring disclos=
ure by securities issuers, and the disclosure rules are not well adapted to=
 crypto, meaning that even a non-swindle crypto project will have a hard ti=
me registering its tokens and complying with US law.</li>=09<li style=3D"ma=
rgin-bottom: 5px;">The law empowers the US Securities and Exchange Commissi=
on to regulate securities, and <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/34967840.259352/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
